    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I think it's not that ufuncs cause `pd.DataFrame` to lose its sparse type, but it is lost as soon as the copy is made with a `pd.DataFrame` constructor because they're different classes (similar to #23744).\r\n```\r\n>>> df = pd.SparseDataFrame(np.array([[0, 1, 0], [0, 0, 0], [0, 0, 1]]), columns=list('abc'), default_fill_value=0)\r\n>>> df2 = pd.DataFrame(df)\r\n>>> type(df)\r\n<class 'pandas.core.sparse.frame.SparseDataFrame'>\r\n>>> type(df2)\r\n<class 'pandas.core.frame.DataFrame'>\r\n```"
  },
